    "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::inconsistent_error_contracts_across_public_apis::a5463fec": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::inconsistent_error_contracts_across_public_apis::a5463fec",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Adjacent public APIs expose conflicting failure contracts (boolean status, panic, and error return), making callers handle similar operations in incompatible ways.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/version.go",
          "goseg/handler/upload.go",
          "goseg/startram/startram.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`CheckVersion()` returns `(structs.Channel, bool)` and suppresses concrete error reasons (`goseg/config/version.go:23`).",
          "`LocalVersion()` panics on file I/O and JSON decode errors (`goseg/config/version.go:131`, `goseg/config/version.go:137`, `goseg/config/version.go:142`).",
          "`UploadHandler()` and StarTram endpoints return `error` values for similar external failures (`goseg/handler/upload.go:12`, `goseg/startram/startram.go:123`)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Standardize exported runtime APIs on `(..., error)` (or `error` only), replace panic paths with propagated errors, and reserve panics for truly unrecoverable startup invariants.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T09:04:04+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T09:04:04+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-01T09:10:05+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::startram_http_contract_drift::d6d7dcd2": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::startram_http_contract_drift::d6d7dcd2",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "StarTram methods that represent the same API layer disagree on whether HTTP status codes are part of the contract, causing inconsistent success/failure behavior.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startram/startram.go",
          "README.md"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`Register`, `SvcCreate`, `SvcDelete`, and `AliasCreate` parse response JSON without checking `resp.StatusCode` (`goseg/startram/startram.go:136`, `goseg/startram/startram.go:185`, `goseg/startram/startram.go:223`, `goseg/startram/startram.go:260`).",
          "`GetBackup` and `UploadBackup` explicitly fail when status is non-200 (`goseg/startram/startram.go:475`, `goseg/startram/startram.go:528`).",
          "README documents operational usage but does not define API failure semantics, leaving this inconsistency unbounded for consumers (`README.md`)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define one transport contract for all StarTram calls (status-first, then payload decode), implement a shared request helper enforcing it, and document expected failure categories.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T09:04:04+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T09:04:04+00:00",
