        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/startram/startram.go` (~900 lines) combines HTTP client operations (`FetchRegions`, `Register`, `GetBackup`), config persistence side effects (`config.UpdateConf`, `config.StartramConfig`), event publication (`EventBus <- ...`), and backup restore internals (`writeBackupToVolume`, archive extraction, docker inspect command execution).",
          "Direct external boundary calls are interleaved with domain logic (`exec.Command` in `writeBackupToVolume`, `os.WriteFile` to `/opt/nativeplanet/groundseg/restore`, and network calls via `http.Get`/`http.Post`) with no adapter boundaries.",
          "By contrast, `goseg/config/version.go` already isolates version-fetch and persistence helpers, showing that startram\u2019s mixed concerns are not forced by project style."
        ],
