      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The StarTram module is a god file owning unrelated domains (API, orchestration, crypto, backup restore, and process execution), obscuring architectural boundaries.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startram/startram.go",
          "goseg/config/version.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "goseg/startram/startram.go is ~900 lines with 25+ functions spanning network API methods, event/cache globals, encryption/decryption, backup download/upload, tar extraction, and docker inspect execution.",
          "The same module both defines public API operations (Register/SvcCreate/AliasCreate) and low-level implementation details (writeBackupToVolume, encryptFile, decryptFile), forcing broad ripple changes for unrelated features.",
          "goseg/config/version.go shows a similar boundary blur (remote fetch + persistence + global mutation), reinforcing missing subsystem decomposition rather than isolated file growth."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split StarTram into focused packages (e.g., `startram/client`, `startram/registry`, `startram/backup`, `startram/state`) and keep the top-level package as a thin orchestration facade. Move version transport/persistence into dedicated `config/versionstore` + `config/versionclient` components with explicit interfaces.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
