        "evidence": [
          "`UploadHandler` decodes websocket payloads and directly invokes `importer.SetUploadSession`/`importer.Reset` based on string action values (`upload.go:19-26`).",
          "`SyncRetrieve` performs retrieval plus direct config mutation and event publication (`startram.go:122-138`), coupling one call path to multiple subsystems.",
          "Both patterns force cross-module coordination through direct package calls and stringly command branching, increasing change coupling between protocol handlers and runtime state modules."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce application-service interfaces between handlers and subsystems (e.g., `UploadService`, `StartramService`) and map transport actions to typed commands at the edge. Keep state mutation/event emission behind those services to preserve boundary integrity.",
