      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Cross-module state is coordinated through mutable package globals rather than explicit state services.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/version.go",
          "goseg/startram/startram.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`config/version.go` defines package globals `VersionServerReady` and `VersionInfo` and mutates them inside `SyncVersionInfo`.",
          "`startram/startram.go` defines global `Regions` map and replaces it in `SyncRegions`.",
          "These globals are part of public package surface and become implicit synchronization points for other modules, increasing hidden coupling and change blast radius."
        ],
