      "summary": "WiFi module mixes OS command orchestration, AP lifecycle, websocket request handling, and periodic broadcast loops in one package surface.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/system/wifi.go",
          "goseg/accesspoint/accesspoint_test.go",
          "goseg/system/system.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`C2CMode`, `C2CConnect`, and `UnaliveC2C` orchestrate system services and shell commands, while `CaptiveAPI` handles websocket protocol parsing and `announceNetworks` manages long-lived client broadcasts in the same file.",
          "`C2CConnect` includes system reboot side effects (`execCommandForWiFi(\"reboot\")`), while `CaptiveAPI` may also restart groundseg, indicating competing lifecycle paths in transport-facing code.",
