          "goseg/config/config.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`configService` methods in `shipcreator.go` are direct one-line forwards (`Conf`, `UrbitConf`, `UrbitConfAll`, `UpdateUrbitConfig`, `UpdatePiers`) to global `config` package functions.",
          "Top-level shipcreator functions use `defaultService = NewService(nil)`, so callers still depend on a global concrete implementation instead of dependency-selected boundaries.",
          "`importer/importer.go` calls package-level shipcreator functions, which bypass explicit dependency wiring at call sites."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either remove `ConfigService` and call `config` directly (reduce indirection), or make the boundary honest: inject `Service` explicitly where used (e.g., importer/handlers), eliminate global `defaultService`, and define a narrower interface around only operations needed by each caller.",
        "reasoning": ""
