        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`NewShipHandler` handles domain flow but, for cancel, constructs a websocket payload, marshals it, and re-enters `UrbitHandler` instead of invoking a shared domain operation directly.",
          "`handleStartramToggle` builds `WsUrbitPayload`, marshals JSON, and dispatches to `UrbitHandler` inside orchestration loops, coupling startram behavior to urbit transport contracts.",
          "Action handlers publish UI event strings inline while also mutating system state, so protocol changes and business behavior changes are entangled."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce handler-independent application services (e.g., `ShipService`) and make handlers only parse/validate payloads and call typed service methods; centralize websocket event mapping in a separate adapter layer.",
