      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Upload action protocol is duplicated as raw strings across handler and service test, creating boundary drift risk.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/upload.go",
          "goseg/uploadsvc/service_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`uploadActionOpenEndpoint` is defined in `handler/upload.go`, while `service_test.go` uses the raw literal `\"open-endpoint\"` directly.",
          "Routing behavior in `Handle` depends on exact string matching, so contract changes require synchronized edits across packages with no compile-time guard."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Move upload action identifiers into a shared typed contract (e.g., constants/type in `uploadsvc` or `structs`) and update handler/tests to consume that single source so mismatches fail at compile/test boundaries earlier.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
