    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::contract_and_adapter_co_located_in_uploadsvc::3ddfca3c": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::contract_and_adapter_co_located_in_uploadsvc::3ddfca3c",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Service contract and concrete importer adapter are merged in one package/file.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go",
          "goseg/handler/upload.go",
          "goseg/startram/errors.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`uploadsvc` exports `Service` but also ships `ImporterService` that directly invokes importer package functions, so the same package owns both abstraction and infrastructure detail.",
          "`handler/upload.go` depends on this mixed package for both action contract (`ActionOpenEndpoint`, `ActionReset`) and runtime behavior (`service.OpenEndpoint`/`Reset`).",
          "`startram/errors.go` shows a separate package-specific boundary wrapper (`wrapAPIConnectionError`) while upload path lacks an equivalent boundary-specific adapter layer, indicating inconsistent boundary ownership across subsystems."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split upload service contract/types from importer-backed implementation: keep `uploadsvc` as contract-only (interfaces, request types, actions), move `ImporterService` to a separate adapter package (for example `uploadsvc/importeradapter`), and wire it at composition/root level.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
