          "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go",
          "goseg/handler/startram.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/handler/support.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`createUrbitShip`, multiple urbit operation handlers, and startram handlers all publish transitions/events directly, perform core operations, then sleep and clear status in the same functions.",
          "`runImportPhases` plus `errorCleanup` in importer ties lifecycle execution to websocket transition emission instead of separating orchestration from business actions.",
          "`SupportHandler` interleaves bug-report file work, profiling, upload transport, and transition timing (`time.Sleep`) in one request path."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce a shared operation-orchestrator abstraction (phase runner + standardized transition policy) and keep handlers focused on invoking domain use-cases; move sleep/clear semantics into one reusable transition policy component.",
