      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Failure rollback logic for ship provisioning is copied into separate cleanup routines, increasing drift risk.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/newship.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`newship.errorCleanup` and `importer.errorCleanup` both remove configs, update system entries, and delete volumes with near-parallel structure.",
          "Deletion/stop/recovery concerns also appear in `deleteShip`, `togglePower`, `rebuildContainer`, and `urbitCleanDelete` with overlapping but non-identical sequencing.",
          "Rollback behavior is encoded per workflow rather than as reusable compensating actions."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Create a shared ship-lifecycle compensation module (idempotent steps for config removal, container teardown, volume/custom-path cleanup, transition emission) and compose it from workflows instead of duplicating procedural cleanup blocks.",
