    "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::dc-dup-01::ebb1c7bb": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::dc-dup-01::ebb1c7bb",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Duplicate transition orchestration helpers create parallel lifecycle semantics across modules.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/workflow.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/startram.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/handler/workflow.go` defines generic helpers for publish/error transitions (`publishTransitionWithPolicy`, `runTransitionedOperation`), but `goseg/shipworkflow/startram.go` implements its own transition utility (`publishTransition`) and bespoke per-step transition/error mapping in the same domain.",
          "`goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go` calls shared transition helpers in some places while also handling local state/cleanup transitions in nearby functions, increasing semantic drift across paths."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce a single lifecycle transition service in one package and require all ship workflows (startram + urbit operations) to use it for begin/in-progress/success/error/clear transitions, including common delay/clear policies.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T16:08:35+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T16:08:35+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-01T17:05:12+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null,
      "resolution_attestation": {
        "kind": "scan_verified",
        "text": "Disappeared from detector output",
        "attested_at": "2026-03-01T17:05:12+00:00",
        "scan_verified": true
      }
    },
    "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::dc-dup-02::2a35dc40": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::dc-dup-02::2a35dc40",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Pack lifecycle orchestration is duplicated between scheduled routines and ship operations.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go",
          "goseg/routines/pack.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`packPier` and `packMeldPier` in `goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go` each perform local transition initialization, deferred clear/publish behavior, status checks, and wait loops.",
          "`goseg/routines/pack.go` (`setScheduledPackTimer`) implements similar event/polling/transition patterns for packing operations, with repeated wait and status/error handling logic.",
          "These modules also diverge in naming and local error wrapping details, making behavior consistency hard to guarantee."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a common packing lifecycle abstraction (e.g., `PackOperationCoordinator`) that standardizes transition emission, status polling, and clear/error semantics, then wire both immediate and scheduled pack flows through it.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T16:08:35+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T16:08:35+00:00",
