    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_seam_duplication::ebdec742": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_seam_duplication::ebdec742",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Runtime seam structs duplicate thin pass-through wrappers across container workflows, creating unearned indirection",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/docker/docker.go",
          "goseg/routines/docker.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/docker/runtime_seams.go` defines `wireguardRuntime`, `netdataRuntime`, `minioRuntime`, and `urbitRuntime` with many function fields that simply forward to package-level helpers (for example `writeWgConf: func(rt wireguardRuntime) error { return writeWgConfWithRuntime(rt) }`).",
          "`goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go` repeats a similar pattern for `dockerRoutineRuntime` and `versionRuntime`, again wrapping direct package functions without behavioral translation.",
          "Call paths (`LoadWireguard()`, `wgContainerConf()`, `wgContainerConfWithRuntime`, `dockerSubscriptionHandler(newDockerRoutineRuntime())`) add extra construction and delegation hops before reaching actual logic."
        ],
