      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Timeout handling is determined by string matching on `err.Error()`, creating brittle and non-authoritative error contracts.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/importer/extract.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "The importer maps outcomes with a substring check (`strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"timed out\")`), then emits a specific status code.",
          "This makes behavior depend on textual formatting rather than typed sentinel/wrapped errors and can silently misclassify unrelated errors that happen to contain that phrase."
        ],
