      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Broadcast uses mutable package-level function/variable seams that leak test-only indirection into production behavior.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
          "goseg/leak/broadcast.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/collectors_and_mappers.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`broadcast.go` exposes mutable globals used as seams (for example loop-related helpers and configurable constructors) that are reassigned in tests, making runtime behavior depend on shared mutable package state.",
          "`leak/broadcast.go` also maintains package-global channels/state (`BytesChan`, status sink structures) and ad-hoc sender wiring instead of explicit instance-scoped collaborators.",
          "The seam pattern is uneven across files in the same area, so some paths go through helpers while others call concrete implementations directly."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace process-global seam vars with an explicit `BroadcastRuntime` interface and inject an instance into loop/sender startup. Keep only immutable dependencies in `loop` and `send` structs, and pass sink/state per call path so tests can substitute mocks without mutating package-level globals.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
