    "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::config_god_module::0c47c9ab": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::config_god_module::0c47c9ab",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Split `config` into boot/runtime state and feature-specific config writers to avoid mixed responsibilities",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/config.go",
          "goseg/config/mc.go",
          "goseg/config/version.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/config/config.go` owns process bootstrap (`init()`, `initializeConfig`, `initializePaths`), mutable global runtime state (`globalConfig`, `BasePath`, `Conf()`, multiple mutexes), persistence (`persistConf`, `UpdateConfTyped`), and domain snapshots for every subsystem.",
          "`goseg/config/mc.go` and `goseg/config/version.go` mutate feature-specific config files by directly reading global config state (`BasePath`, `confForMc`, `getVersionChannelForMc`) and performing file I/O in the same package.",
          "A single change in config loading or storage layout requires touching global and feature behavior in the same module family, making separation and testability weaker."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce explicit boundaries: a `configbootstrap` module for startup and env/path setup, a `configstore` module for typed config persistence/state synchronization, and per-feature adapters (`mc`, `version`) that receive dependencies rather than reaching into globals.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
