      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Archive extraction paths are split by extension with near-duplicate control logic rather than a shared extraction strategy abstraction.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/importer/extract.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`extractUploadedPier` switches on extensions and delegates to separate extractor functions, then each extractor performs similar event-loop/progress behavior inline.",
          "`extractZip`, `extractTarGz`, and `extractTar` each manually reimplement timeout setup, directory creation, entry filtering, output writes, and progress publishing details with slight behavioral drift.",
          "Progress semantics differ between implementations (`fileCount`/size weighting differs per extractor), making extension handlers harder to reason about as independent policy changes evolve."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce a common extraction strategy interface with shared archive traversal helpers and a single progress publisher; keep format-specific handlers focused only on parsing/writer-specific reader behavior to reduce duplicated abstraction depth.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
