      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Auth token payload map declares duplicate `token` key, risking invalid compile/contract behavior.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/auth/auth.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`CreateToken` sets `\"token\"` twice in the same map literal, making the entry definition ambiguous and likely a real compile-time defect in Go map construction.",
          "Import path consumers in `importer` expect a single stable token mapping (`Token.ID`, `Token.Token`) and the duplicate obscures intended token output shape."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove the duplicate key and keep a single canonical `Token` entry; if additional encoded fields are needed, use distinct map keys or a typed payload struct and validate consumers in importer accordingly.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:19:05+00:00",
