    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::marshal-failure-misreported-success::2a23995e": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::marshal-failure-misreported-success::2a23995e",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Broadcast update returns success when payload marshal fails, masking mutation failure.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/leak/broadcast.go",
          "goseg/leak/broadcast_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`updateBroadcast` logs `json.Marshal(newBroadcast)` errors and returns `oldBroadcast, nil` rather than propagating an error.",
          "`updateBroadcast` also checks per-recipient `wrapperUrbitBytes, err := json.Marshal(wrappedUrbit)` and only sends on nil, but never returns/report this failure to callers.",
          "Tests in `goseg/leak/broadcast_test.go` validate `updateBroadcast` error behavior but do not observe partial-failure telemetry when marshalling fails, so this silent path is unobservable to callers."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Return a wrapped error when either marshal fails, and keep the function output explicit about failed updates (e.g., return unchanged state + error). Also propagate/aggregate per-recipient marshal failures so broadcast callers can react or alert on partial fanout failure.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:19:05+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:19:05+00:00",
