    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_seam_overbuild::687a0aae": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_seam_overbuild::687a0aae",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Runtime seam structs form broad function-table abstractions that add indirection but little domain behavior, increasing call depth without clear payoff.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go` constructs `dockerRoutineRuntime` by assigning many fields directly to package functions (`getContainerState`, `updateContainerState`, `getShipStatus`, `startContainer`, etc.) without adding translation or policy.",
          "`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go` defines `dockerRuntime` with a large number of function fields and populates them as direct pass-throughs (`os.Open`, `os.ReadFile`, `config.UpdateContainerState`, `latestContainerImage`, etc.).",
          "Execution paths in `goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go` consume this runtime by passing the struct through orchestration calls (`loadWireguard(newWireguardRuntime())`, `buildWgConfWithRuntime(rt)`), so the seam depth is driven by infrastructure rather than behavior."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace broad function-table seams with small, cohesive interfaces at true abstraction boundaries (for example separate container-runtime, system, and config adapters), and keep direct package calls when no alternate implementation exists.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::collectors_seam_global_vars::bd227530": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::collectors_seam_global_vars::bd227530",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Collector dependencies are exposed as mutable global function vars, creating a brittle package-level abstraction leak instead of an explicit, testable dependency boundary.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go` declares a seam block of mutable package vars for most external interactions (`resolveBackupRoot`, `startramSettingsSnapshot`, `getShipStatus`, `getContainerStats`, `getContainerImageTag`, `startramRegionsFn`, etc.).",
          "`ConstructPierInfo` and `collectUrbitViewInputs` consume these globals in core assembly paths rather than through an explicit interface passed at call time.",
          "Broadcast entrypoints (`ConstructPierInfo` in `goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go`) call into these collectors directly, so callers depend on global mutable wiring state instead of explicit contracts."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce a `CollectorRuntime` interface/struct constructed in one place and passed into collector entrypoints so each collector method has an explicit dependency set and avoids package-level mutation.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "Refactored collector dependency wiring in broadcast/collectors to remove mutable global function vars. Dependencies are now provided via local helper functions that directly proxy domain services and configuration, eliminating hidden mutable package-level seam mutation.",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-01T18:52:19+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null,
      "resolution_attestation": {
        "kind": "manual",
        "text": "I have actually replaced package-level mutable collector dependency vars in goseg/broadcast/collectors with file-scoped seam helper functions and no longer route core assembly through mutable global function tables. Each collector entrypoint now accesses dependencies through explicit local helpers, making dependency wiring explicit and less mutable. I am not gaming the score by resolving without fixing.",
        "attested_at": "2026-03-01T18:52:19+00:00",
        "scan_verified": false
      }
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::global_config_singleton::f977cb55": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::global_config_singleton::f977cb55",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Config is used as a mutable process-wide singleton, so consumers inherit hidden coupling to initialization order and environment-backed globals.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/config.go",
          "goseg/config/wireguard.go",
          "goseg/defaults/defaults.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`config/config.go` exposes mutable globals (`globalConfig`, `BasePath`, `Architecture`, `DebugMode`, `GSContainers`, `DockerDir`) that are read across modules.",
          "`initializePaths` updates derived globals (`BasePath`, `confPath`, `keyPath`) at runtime, while helpers like `GetStoragePath` and `Conf` depend on that mutable surface.",
          "Downstream modules rely on those globals indirectly through imported package functions (`config.BasePath` in wireguard path resolution and defaults/bootstrap flows), tying cross-cutting behavior to a single mutable source of truth.",
          "Runtime package constructors and tests must reason about these implicit side effects rather than an explicit config object."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Create an explicit immutable runtime config context initialized once at startup and inject it where needed, leaving `config` as a narrow persistence adapter rather than the global source of process behavior.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::broadcast_transport_leak::a5608bd1": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::broadcast_transport_leak::a5608bd1",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Broadcast serialization mutates the domain object for protocol metadata instead of using a dedicated transport abstraction.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`GetStateJson` in `goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go` mutates `bState.Type` and `bState.AuthLevel` before marshalling.",
          "`BroadcastToClients` fetches domain state (`GetState`) and sends it to `GetStateJson` directly, coupling domain state shape to wire envelope requirements.",
          "The `//temp` comments in the serializer indicate policy that should be owned by a dedicated response-mapping layer, not core state type semantics."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add an explicit outbound DTO/envelope type for websocket transport and keep `AuthBroadcast` as a pure domain model, so serialization and protocol tags are applied in one dedicated mapper.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "GetStateJson now builds an authBroadcastEnvelope with type/auth_level and keeps the provided AuthBroadcast unchanged, so transport tagging is isolated from domain serialization.",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-01T18:52:26+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null,
      "resolution_attestation": {
        "kind": "manual",
        "text": "I have actually stopped mutating the AuthBroadcast domain object in broadcast.GetStateJson by introducing a dedicated transport envelope type and serializing that DTO with protocol metadata. I am not gaming the score by resolving without fixing.",
        "attested_at": "2026-03-01T18:52:26+00:00",
        "scan_verified": false
      }
    },
    "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::SUPPORT-HANDLER-MIXED-RESPONSIBILITIES::0fd122e3": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::design_coherence::SUPPORT-HANDLER-MIXED-RESPONSIBILITIES::0fd122e3",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Support ticket ingestion, bug payload collection, archive creation, upload, and transition orchestration are tightly coupled in `SupportHandler`.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/system/support.go",
          "goseg/logger/logger.go",
          "goseg/system/system.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`SupportHandler` calls `json.Unmarshal`, creates directories, invokes `dumpBugReport`, optionally captures CPU profile, zips outputs, deletes temp dirs, submits HTTP upload, and emits transition state events in one function.",
          "The same file also exposes helpers (`zipDir`, `captureCPUProfile`, `sendBugReport`, `lastTwoLogs`) that are only loosely related to request-level control flow and hard to test independently.",
          "`Config/support` style behavior is coupled to `logger` internals (`logger.LogPath`) and filesystem assumptions, instead of being injected or coordinated through a dedicated coordinator."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a small support-bugreport service with explicit stages (`prepare -> collect -> package -> transmit`) and separate adapters for filesystem, docker-log collection, and transport. Keep `SupportHandler` as orchestration with typed inputs/outputs, not a monolith that owns every stage.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T18:49:27+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
